### Description

When my model is a discriminate union:
```ts
interface TestA {
  type: 'a';
  a: number;
}

interface TestB {
  type: 'b';
  b: string;
}

type Tester = TestA | TestB;
```
And I want to render the form controls conditionally based on type in a component... I am pretty sure there is no way to do it right now:
```ts
@Component({
  selector: 'app-test',
  template: `
    <!-- How to do the if check with correct types? -->
  `,
  styles: '',
})
export class Test {
  readonly tester = input.required<FieldTree<Tester>>();
}
```
In schema it is easy to do using `applyWhenValue`:
```ts
form(signal<Tester>({...}), path => {
  applyWhenValue(path, v => v.type === 'a', aPath => required(aPath.a))
})
```

### Proposed solution

Allow to somehow infer the correct discriminate union case in the template like `applyWhenValue` in the schema.

